03:11.225 --> 03:13.761
Where are we going?

03:17.298 --> 03:21.778
Mabel. La Tía Mabel.

03:21.802 --> 03:25.482
What?
La Tía Mabel.

03:25.506 --> 03:27.341
Your bell?

03:29.377 --> 03:33.357
I don't... Uh, um...

03:33.381 --> 03:42.366
No habla español.

03:44.958 --> 03:47.371
It's hard to focus.
I'm so scared right now.

04:26.734 --> 04:30.103
Is this your buddy?
Is this your friend?

05:00.601 --> 05:02.879
Guess what.
You're not special.

05:02.903 --> 05:04.348
In the U.S. alone,

05:04.372 --> 05:06.516
there are 4.2 million
recreational artists,

05:06.540 --> 05:11.220
800,000 art students,
and 3 million professionals.

05:11.244 --> 05:15.224
That's 8 million people
infected with the disease

05:15.248 --> 05:19.219
that some optimistically call
"the creative type."

05:21.389 --> 05:23.199
They wake up every morning, and
when they look in the mirror,

05:23.223 --> 05:25.369
they feel special.

05:25.393 --> 05:28.204
They think they have
a story worth telling.

05:28.228 --> 05:31.174
Most of them go on and write,
paint, play, sing the story,

05:31.198 --> 05:33.410
and then they publish it
on endless blogs.

05:33.434 --> 05:36.346
The world tells them,
"Trust yourself,"

05:36.370 --> 05:38.582
and "You are different."

05:38.606 --> 05:40.584
But only 15% of them
will get a job

05:40.608 --> 05:42.386
that they feel worthy
of their talent.

05:42.410 --> 05:45.254
A mere 2% will achieve
any sort of visibility.

05:45.278 --> 05:48.057
And less than .2%
will get famous,

05:48.081 --> 05:51.495
only to be forgotten in
an average time of three years.

05:51.519 --> 05:53.697
Before traveling
to Argentina that winter,

05:53.721 --> 05:55.432
I was among these
8 million people.

05:55.456 --> 05:57.367
I met Sofia for the first time

05:57.391 --> 06:00.404
when she left a comment
on my most famous viral video...

06:00.428 --> 06:02.171
"Dancing Tomatoes."

06:02.195 --> 06:04.774
She wrote,
"Your work is so shallow,

06:04.798 --> 06:07.444
it's the perfect metaphor
for a decadent world."

06:07.468 --> 06:09.437
I was instantly
attracted to her.

06:15.242 --> 06:17.887
If he buys this,
we're finally set, Alex.

06:17.911 --> 06:20.356
No more of this
struggling artist bullshit.

06:20.380 --> 06:21.991
We need this, man.

06:22.015 --> 06:24.193
Alex, I need you to focus, okay?

06:24.217 --> 06:26.029
It's definitely
a big opportunity,

06:26.053 --> 06:28.565
but just pitch the show
with a lot of confidence

06:28.589 --> 06:30.834
and you'll be fine.
Say yes.

06:30.858 --> 06:32.669
Yes. Yes.
That's it.

06:32.693 --> 06:34.604
Come on.

06:34.628 --> 06:36.039
You just really need
to focus, that's all.

06:37.898 --> 06:40.076
Look, I brought the tomatoes
in case you want to use them.

06:40.100 --> 06:41.611
Here.

06:41.635 --> 06:45.214
You know, he might want
to see them or something.

06:45.238 --> 06:47.407
All right, man. Let's go.
Let's do this. Come on.

06:49.677 --> 06:51.755
Why are we doing this?
That's the main question, right?

06:51.779 --> 06:54.390
I want to respect
the artistic process.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.392
I want to do more than, like,
a funny video or, like,

06:56.416 --> 06:58.495
a dancing thing, you know?

06:58.519 --> 07:00.229
I know what I don't want to do.

07:00.253 --> 07:02.031
I have a long list
of things that I hate.

07:02.055 --> 07:03.900
It doesn't have to be
overly negative, of course.

07:03.924 --> 07:08.705
How many viewers does your
tomatoes video have up to now?

07:08.729 --> 07:10.440
Uh, it's like 2 million.

07:10.464 --> 07:11.741
But it's been online
for three years.

07:11.765 --> 07:13.677
And how much money
have you made?

07:13.701 --> 07:15.378
It's online.
Nada?

07:15.402 --> 07:16.946
Zip?
Zero?

07:16.970 --> 07:19.716
In the old days,
fame came with fortune.

07:19.740 --> 07:21.851
Internet fame costs you money.

07:21.875 --> 07:23.887
You're paying for
other people to enjoy.

07:23.911 --> 07:25.421
I'm glad you brought it up,

07:25.445 --> 07:26.823
'cause he and I
talk about this all the time.

07:26.847 --> 07:29.025
Do you know about
what our brand is?

07:29.049 --> 07:30.860
Energy Yogurt...
I assume it's yogurt.

07:30.884 --> 07:32.395
Yeah.

07:32.419 --> 07:34.931
We're gonna sign a contract,
you and me.

07:34.955 --> 07:36.866
I can get it ready for you
in a couple of weeks.

07:36.890 --> 07:38.367
The point is,
is that you're gonna have

07:38.391 --> 07:40.537
complete artistic freedom, okay?

07:40.561 --> 07:42.606
The only thing we're gonna do
is we're gonna change out

07:42.630 --> 07:45.709
the tomatoes for strawberries,
bananas, and kiwis

07:45.733 --> 07:46.943
just to get a range.

07:46.967 --> 07:48.578
I Fe...

07:48.602 --> 07:50.379
I feel like we're talking
about two different things here.

07:50.403 --> 07:52.381
Uh, well, let's be
honest here, Patrick.

07:52.405 --> 07:54.183
Alex.
Yeah, whatever.

07:54.207 --> 07:57.521
You can milk the tomatoes now
and get the money

07:57.545 --> 07:59.856
or you can watch
how people forget about it

07:59.880 --> 08:01.858
and go on
to the next stupid thing.

08:01.882 --> 08:04.060
Now, do you want
to put it to work for you

08:04.084 --> 08:07.497
or do you want
to let it go to waste?

08:48.762 --> 08:51.340
Yo!
Just a minute.

08:51.364 --> 08:53.342
Come on.
There's a fucking line.

09:12.686 --> 09:16.165
Hey!
Tomato guy, whoo!

09:48.021 --> 09:51.367
This is an automated security
alert from East Borough Bank.

09:51.391 --> 09:53.837
A purchase superior to $1,000

09:53.861 --> 09:55.672
has been charged
to your credit card...

09:55.696 --> 09:57.573
Oh, no.

09:57.597 --> 10:02.111
An American Airlines ticket
to Buenos Aires, Argentina.

10:02.135 --> 10:04.047
If you did not make
this transaction,

10:04.071 --> 10:06.650
please contact us immediately.

10:06.674 --> 10:09.209
Have a great day.

10:15.515 --> 10:18.194
Hey. What's up?
You won't believe what happened.

10:18.218 --> 10:19.829
I've been invited
to talk about my work

10:19.853 --> 10:22.165
in Buenos Aires... tomorrow.

10:22.189 --> 10:23.867
I'd love to see you.

10:23.891 --> 10:26.293
Let me know if you want
to grab a coffee or something.

