11:57.851 --> 11:59.829
♪ La-la-la...

11:59.853 --> 12:01.397
Hi, Sofia.

12:01.421 --> 12:02.899
I'm writing this e-mail
from the phone of a guy

12:02.923 --> 12:05.458
who offered his help.

12:07.560 --> 12:10.697
I just got all my stuff stolen
when I was looking for a hotel.

12:13.633 --> 12:16.345
I'll be sitting on the corner
of Humboldt and Paraguay.

12:16.369 --> 12:18.872
I have no money and no way
to get back to you.

12:20.874 --> 12:22.251
I know this is the last message

12:22.275 --> 12:24.077
you were expecting
to get from me.

12:28.515 --> 12:29.859
I promise it will be
the last one

12:29.883 --> 12:32.161
if you don't show up.

12:32.185 --> 12:33.362
I'll be waiting.

12:33.386 --> 12:35.722
Yours, Alex.

14:07.280 --> 14:10.426
Fundamental dynamics
of our eye contact.

14:10.450 --> 14:12.095
The dynamics of our eye contact

14:12.119 --> 14:15.398
started 8,000 years ago
in the interior of the sun.

14:15.422 --> 14:17.733
Millions of photons were trapped
in its core for centuries,

14:17.757 --> 14:20.836
and, much later, we were born
and everything else happened.

14:20.860 --> 14:22.671
Then in a solar storm
eight minutes

14:22.695 --> 14:24.540
before I saw her
for the first time

14:24.564 --> 14:26.109
that summer night,
some of those photons

14:26.133 --> 14:28.444
traveled 91.4 million miles
through space

14:28.468 --> 14:29.778
and bounced into the moon,

14:29.802 --> 14:32.248
reaching my pupils
1.3 seconds later.

14:32.272 --> 14:34.350
Only then, a portion
of those particles

14:34.374 --> 14:35.851
reflected back to Sofia.

14:35.875 --> 14:37.520
And so, we could look each other

14:37.544 --> 14:39.188
in the eyes for the first time.

14:39.212 --> 14:41.581
But the fact of the matter
is that I looked away.

14:43.550 --> 14:46.562
Hi.

14:46.586 --> 14:49.332
Hi.

14:49.356 --> 14:54.437
Are you okay?

14:54.461 --> 14:57.530
I'm okay.

15:01.234 --> 15:04.413
Eh, why would you call me
in a situation like this?

15:04.437 --> 15:06.182
What about the people
you came to see?

15:06.206 --> 15:09.252
I-I-I lost all my stuff.

15:09.276 --> 15:11.054
And I-I didn't have
anyone else's e-mail,

15:11.078 --> 15:12.521
so I'm sorry.
I'm not...

15:12.545 --> 15:16.759
Did he mention Mabel?
Mabel? What, uh...

15:16.783 --> 15:19.762
Did Victor ask you something
about my aunt Mabel?

15:19.786 --> 15:21.330
Yeah, Victor...
That's that guy?

15:21.354 --> 15:24.733
That's that... that...
Who is that guy?

15:24.757 --> 15:26.869
It's my boyfriend, okay?

15:26.893 --> 15:28.037
Listen...
Your boyfriend?

15:28.061 --> 15:29.538
Okay, what did you say?

15:29.562 --> 15:31.774
Well, I didn't...
I didn't know what to say.

15:31.798 --> 15:33.576
I thought he was talking
about a fucking bell.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.344
That... he... you...
You have a boyfriend?

15:35.368 --> 15:36.946
I can't believe
that you didn't tell me...

15:36.970 --> 15:38.714
Okay, lower your voice.
That you have a boyfriend.

15:38.738 --> 15:41.017
Shh. Lower your voice.

15:41.041 --> 15:44.053
Listen carefully. I don't know
you and you don't know me, okay?

15:44.077 --> 15:45.521
Clearly.

15:45.545 --> 15:46.755
Tomorrow, you will
make some phone calls

15:46.779 --> 15:50.159
and sleep somewhere else.

15:50.183 --> 15:54.097
What's that?

15:54.121 --> 15:55.564
It's my little bag of shit

15:55.588 --> 15:57.866
that they let me keep
for emotional value.

15:57.890 --> 15:59.102
I-I don't...
I-I-I can't believe

15:59.126 --> 16:00.569
that you lied to me...
I didn't.

16:00.593 --> 16:02.038
About having a boyfriend.
You didn't?

16:02.062 --> 16:03.506
I didn't lie.

16:03.530 --> 16:04.940
What are you talking about?
I didn't lie.

16:04.964 --> 16:06.275
This is my real life.

16:06.299 --> 16:08.111
It's not the Internet.
What?

16:08.135 --> 16:10.079
The Internet is real life.
We've been chatting for months.

16:10.103 --> 16:12.415
I sent you a picture
of my dick 24 hours ago.

16:12.439 --> 16:14.483
What do you expect
out of that picture?

16:14.507 --> 16:15.718
What did I expect?

16:15.742 --> 16:17.086
Five-star hotel
and a loving girlfriend?

16:17.110 --> 16:20.889
I was in a club
in a bathroom in a stall.

16:20.913 --> 16:23.359
And there was a dude
pounding on the door.

16:23.383 --> 16:25.228
Okay, listen.
Okay, yeah, I'm sorry.

16:25.252 --> 16:28.664
Listen. You are my cousin
that I've never seen before.

16:29.722 --> 16:32.868
Aunt Mabel's nephew. Okay?

16:32.892 --> 16:34.270
You can spend the night here

16:34.294 --> 16:39.042
as long as you
play along with this.

16:39.066 --> 16:41.377
Okay?
Okay.

16:41.401 --> 16:47.650
Okay, I have no, uh...
I have no other options, so...

16:47.674 --> 16:49.609
It will be fine.

17:02.122 --> 17:04.166
Hey. Alex?

17:04.191 --> 17:07.103
I'm Flor. Nice to meet you.

17:08.528 --> 17:10.073
Sofia told me about your loss.

17:10.097 --> 17:11.940
I'm so sorry.

17:11.964 --> 17:13.876
She told me
that you live in New York.

17:13.900 --> 17:16.712
I have never been there,
but it must be awesome.

17:16.736 --> 17:20.215
My loss?
Yeah, the robbery, Alex?

17:20.240 --> 17:22.942
Right.

17:27.714 --> 17:31.260
What time is it?
It's, um, 12:50.

17:31.284 --> 17:33.829
You know, I can tell the time
without looking.

17:33.853 --> 17:36.732
I can feel it, you know?
It just happens.

17:36.756 --> 17:39.868
Oh, Alex, if I say
your name a lot, like,

17:39.892 --> 17:42.895
it's just
a memory technique I use.

18:00.012 --> 18:01.514
No, gracias.

18:04.251 --> 18:06.085
What?

18:10.257 --> 18:12.268
Alex, could you move
a little bit?

18:12.292 --> 18:13.536
'Cause we need more room here.

18:13.560 --> 18:15.595
Yes, yes, yes.

18:19.199 --> 18:20.443
Alex, I'm so sorry.

18:20.467 --> 18:22.111
No, no, no.

18:22.135 --> 18:25.138
Alex, I'm sorry.
Go back to sleep.

18:32.212 --> 18:34.390
Alex, I'm sorry.
This is your house, too, okay?

18:34.414 --> 18:35.691
It's not my house.

18:35.715 --> 18:37.025
You can sleep
until the hour you want.

18:37.049 --> 18:38.694
I'm awake. I'm awake.
Come, please.

18:38.718 --> 18:41.521
No, no, no,
I'm not gonna go back to sleep.

18:48.361 --> 18:50.273
Oh. Oh.

18:50.297 --> 18:51.574
I'm sorry.

18:51.598 --> 18:53.176
Why are you sorry?
I-I'm very sorry.

18:53.200 --> 18:54.577
Because you were sleeping.

18:54.601 --> 18:56.035
I don't even know
where I am right now.

19:00.407 --> 19:02.275
She has reason.

19:12.685 --> 19:15.331
A fire.

19:15.355 --> 19:19.835
Fire? Were we starting a fire?
A fire, help.

19:19.859 --> 19:21.504
Help, you, eh?

19:21.528 --> 19:22.938
You here, okay?
You here, you help.

19:22.962 --> 19:25.541
Okay, Victor, okay.
Alex, please go with him.

19:25.565 --> 19:27.176
Go.
Just a minute.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.111
Gonna start a fire somewhere?
Eh, no, you just...

19:29.135 --> 19:31.347
Go. Okay? Go.

19:31.371 --> 19:33.940
Go, go.

19:42.715 --> 19:44.384
What?

19:56.429 --> 19:58.674
Listen, I'm from New Jersey.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.677
I have never done anything...
I have no idea what I'm doing.

20:01.701 --> 20:03.403
Okay? No idea.

20:38.905 --> 20:41.149
Um, Alex?

20:41.173 --> 20:44.577
Um, hola.
Could you come for a second?

20:47.780 --> 20:52.094
Um... I looked up
the U.S. Embassy number

20:52.118 --> 20:54.597
for you to report
your passport missing.

20:54.621 --> 20:57.766
Oh. Thank you.
No, you're welcome.

20:57.790 --> 21:00.769
You know, it's important
that we call now.

21:00.793 --> 21:03.606
Want me to call? You know,
they can steal your identity.

21:03.630 --> 21:05.173
You know that?
That that happens?

21:05.197 --> 21:06.275
Yeah, you know what,
I thought about that.

21:06.299 --> 21:08.176
I'll just do it,
but I don't think

21:08.200 --> 21:09.712
there's any, like,
tremendous rush.

21:09.736 --> 21:12.080
No, really, I read it,
and there was this guy

21:12.104 --> 21:13.582
that was raped in jail

21:13.606 --> 21:15.718
for a crime
that he didn't commit.

21:15.742 --> 21:17.686
Sure, but here's the thing.
What?

21:17.710 --> 21:22.858
Um, I saw with my own eyes
the guy...

21:22.882 --> 21:24.593
They were kids who robbed me.

21:24.617 --> 21:26.362
And I just don't... I think
they were interested in my cash.

21:26.386 --> 21:27.530
I don't think
they wanted my passport.

21:27.554 --> 21:28.897
You can never know. Really.

21:28.921 --> 21:31.023
I know you can never know...

21:44.303 --> 21:45.781
Thank you, Flor.

21:45.805 --> 21:47.550
You call from my phone,
of course.

21:47.574 --> 21:50.218
No, no. What we'll do
is we'll do it later, though.

21:50.242 --> 21:51.654
I don't...

21:55.915 --> 21:58.861
Yeah, I can't...
I can't hear anything.

21:58.885 --> 22:00.162
Let's just call later.

22:00.186 --> 22:02.230
Because it's tricky
to get reception.

22:02.254 --> 22:03.599
You see this bow?
Uh-huh.

22:03.623 --> 22:05.368
You get reception here.
Wait.

22:05.392 --> 22:07.169
Lost or stolen passports...

22:07.193 --> 22:08.937
Choose from the following
options.

22:08.961 --> 22:11.674
Please say "robbery"
if your passport was stolen.

22:11.698 --> 22:14.543
Or say "lost" if your passport
is just missing.

22:14.567 --> 22:17.045
Robbery.
You chose stolen passport.

22:17.069 --> 22:19.715
Please say "violent robbery"
if your life was in peril.

22:19.739 --> 22:22.385
Or say "non-violent"...
Non-violent.

22:22.409 --> 22:24.019
You chose non-violent.

22:24.043 --> 22:25.754
Please wait on the line.

22:25.778 --> 22:27.356
Please state your name
after the beep

22:27.380 --> 22:28.924
as a signature of your testimony

22:28.948 --> 22:31.159
and your passport
will be invalidated.

22:33.620 --> 22:35.431
Um...

22:35.455 --> 22:37.600
Uh, you know what?
I don't know which...

22:37.624 --> 22:39.201
'cause I have a hyphenated...
What do you mean?

22:39.225 --> 22:40.703
I don't, um...
Alex, say your name.

22:40.727 --> 22:42.337
Alex Taylor.

22:42.361 --> 22:44.673
Your former passport
is now invalidated.

22:44.697 --> 22:48.176
Please enter the contact
number in Buenos Aires.

22:51.604 --> 22:53.649
Thank you. You will be
contacted with the date

22:53.673 --> 22:55.518
and instructions
for your appointment.

22:55.542 --> 22:57.520
Have a nice day.
Okay.

22:57.544 --> 22:58.887
They'll call us
with appointment day.

22:58.911 --> 23:00.689
Oh, good. When?

23:00.713 --> 23:02.691
I don't know. They didn't say.

23:02.715 --> 23:05.093
So maybe I could just stay
with you for a couple days?

23:05.117 --> 23:06.895
Until...
Non-violent?

23:06.919 --> 23:08.531
From your e-mail, I thought

23:08.555 --> 23:10.433
they put a gun to your head
when they robbed you.

23:10.457 --> 23:12.868
Well, it was intimidating
on a conceptual level, I mean...

23:12.892 --> 23:14.503
Well, assuming violence

23:14.527 --> 23:16.371
just because you're
in South America is so racist.

23:16.395 --> 23:18.273
No, you know what?
It was violent.

23:18.297 --> 23:20.467
It was more violent
than I remembered it.

23:32.111 --> 23:33.746
What?

23:38.350 --> 23:41.697
You're staying.
I am? I am.

23:41.721 --> 23:44.256
Yes.

24:01.941 --> 24:03.519
What are you doing?

24:03.543 --> 24:09.424
Oh, um, well,
I have no summer clothes,

24:09.448 --> 24:12.928
so I'm improvising.

24:12.952 --> 24:14.997
Let me help you.

24:15.021 --> 24:17.524
Could you stand up?
Yeah.

24:21.393 --> 24:23.596
Thanks.
You're welcome.

24:26.132 --> 24:27.943
So are those
your paintings, too?

24:27.967 --> 24:31.213
Oh, yeah, well,
it's Victor's work.

24:31.237 --> 24:33.315
I'm his assistant.

24:33.339 --> 24:37.686
I help him mix the paint.

24:37.710 --> 24:39.555
You know, they're about
the human figure

24:39.579 --> 24:42.591
as a trigger
for, uh, pictorial dialogue.

24:42.615 --> 24:46.562
Sounds... sounds neat.
Sounds really neat.

24:46.586 --> 24:48.330
So let me... I'm just gonna...

24:48.354 --> 24:50.432
I mean, maybe it's just me,
I don't know.

24:50.456 --> 24:53.736
I just notice a real, uh...

24:53.760 --> 24:56.772
tension between Victor
and Sofia.

24:56.796 --> 25:00.576
Oh, yeah, we're all under
a lot of stress these days.

25:00.600 --> 25:02.711
We have a lot of work to finish.

25:02.735 --> 25:05.781
Two days to go, and then we are
out of here for two weeks.

25:05.805 --> 25:08.150
Victor's gonna be part
of a group exhibition

25:08.174 --> 25:10.710
and the winner
will get a grant for life.

25:12.679 --> 25:16.759
Word is Victor's gonna get it,
but he's nervous.

25:16.783 --> 25:20.186
He says the other guy,
Zarazola, is an asshole.

25:22.121 --> 25:25.200
My friend worked in his studio,

25:25.224 --> 25:29.538
and he asked her to blow him.

25:29.562 --> 25:32.040
And she did.

25:32.064 --> 25:33.709
Do you love it here?

25:33.733 --> 25:36.178
Yeah.

25:36.202 --> 25:40.348
So, you're leaving
with Victor for two weeks?

25:40.372 --> 25:42.184
Uh-huh.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.176
Huh.

26:37.730 --> 26:39.775
I'm sorry.

26:39.799 --> 26:41.877
Uh, I didn't mean to interrupt.

26:41.901 --> 26:44.046
No, no, it's okay.

26:44.070 --> 26:46.214
I just needed a pause, you know?

26:46.238 --> 26:47.916
A break.
Yeah, no, I'm not judging you.

26:47.940 --> 26:50.052
Everyone procrastinates.
It's fine.

26:50.076 --> 26:52.020
What is "procrastinate"?

26:52.044 --> 26:54.857
Well, um, procrastination is

26:54.881 --> 26:56.759
when you, uh, do something,

26:56.783 --> 27:00.028
uh, like, uh, play the guitar

27:00.052 --> 27:04.867
to avoid doing something else,
like your work.

27:04.891 --> 27:07.069
Mm.
Mm.

27:07.093 --> 27:08.503
I'm not doing that.
No?

27:08.527 --> 27:11.707
No. I'm working.
Okay. Clearly.

27:11.731 --> 27:14.342
Clearly.

27:14.366 --> 27:18.180
Were you stalking me?
Was I stalking you?

27:18.204 --> 27:20.148
Hmm, yes.

27:20.172 --> 27:21.016
No.

27:21.040 --> 27:22.317
No?
No.

27:22.341 --> 27:24.186
Sure?
I'm pretty sure.

27:24.210 --> 27:28.256
Mm, okay.

27:28.280 --> 27:32.560
Don't, um... don't let me
stop you from playing horribly.

27:32.584 --> 27:33.495
Okay.
Yeah, yeah.

27:33.519 --> 27:36.198
Okay.
Continue.

27:36.222 --> 27:38.691
Listen.
I'm listening.

27:41.227 --> 27:42.938
I can't now.
It's good.

27:42.962 --> 27:44.539
No, it's... keep going.
No, no, somebody...

27:44.563 --> 27:47.710
You got to learn...
You got to start somewhere.

27:47.734 --> 27:49.411
Alex? Are we doing the show?

27:49.435 --> 27:51.413
Man, I need to know.
Yes. Yes.

27:51.437 --> 27:53.716
Yeah, we're doing the...
Yes, we're gonna do the show.

27:53.740 --> 27:55.250
Are you seriously
in Argentina, man?

27:55.274 --> 27:56.852
Listen, I'll be back
in a few days, okay?

27:56.876 --> 28:00.522
I'm... I'm... I'm...
In the meantime, e-mail.

28:00.546 --> 28:02.057
E-mail is better.

28:02.081 --> 28:03.892
Write me, 'cause I can't
hear a word you're saying.

28:03.916 --> 28:07.362
Alex, Alex. Can you hear me?
Are you there?

28:07.386 --> 28:09.732
Josh.

28:09.756 --> 28:11.399
Josh, Josh, Josh, hello?

28:11.423 --> 28:13.960
Buddy?
Hello?

28:21.901 --> 28:24.279
Alex, maybe
if everything goes well

28:24.303 --> 28:26.648
with the paintings,
Victor and I will tour

28:26.672 --> 28:29.184
and we could visit you
in New York.

28:29.208 --> 28:30.385
Oh, it's, uh...

28:30.409 --> 28:33.579
Sofia, could you pass the salad?

28:42.121 --> 28:44.399
Are you going to the, uh,
exhibition with them?

28:44.423 --> 28:46.334
No. I'm staying here.
Oh, you are?

28:46.358 --> 28:48.895
Mm-hmm.

28:52.899 --> 28:54.342
Victor doesn't like the U.S.A.

28:54.366 --> 28:56.544
because he's a Peronist,
you know?

28:56.568 --> 28:58.580
Have you heard... Peronism?
No.

28:58.604 --> 29:00.983
He thinks that
it's an imperialistic country

29:01.007 --> 29:02.717
and that it will fall.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.319
Oh.

29:04.343 --> 29:06.354
Well, you know, yeah.
I mean, I...

29:06.378 --> 29:09.691
Listen, I, yeah, I'm against
all military action,

29:09.715 --> 29:12.227
but I think every country
has its... misery.

29:12.251 --> 29:14.029
I think America's in the
spotlight, of course, because...

29:14.053 --> 29:16.164
You know,
I'm more like an anarchist

29:16.188 --> 29:18.757
because I don't believe
in state that much.

29:26.398 --> 29:27.910
Spotlight?

29:27.934 --> 29:29.544
Yeah, I said spotlight.

29:29.568 --> 29:32.038
Um, why?
America.

29:37.209 --> 29:39.187
America is all the continent.

29:39.211 --> 29:41.223
What does that mean?
All the continent?

29:41.247 --> 29:43.549
No...

30:09.041 --> 30:10.886
What? What?

30:10.910 --> 30:14.756
I think he's saying that you
collaborated with Guantanamo.

30:14.780 --> 30:16.591
Guantanamo. Sí.

30:16.615 --> 30:17.492
Yeah.
No.

30:17.516 --> 30:18.827
In its construction?

30:18.851 --> 30:20.228
I think there's, um,

30:20.252 --> 30:21.997
a lot that's getting
lost in translation.

30:22.021 --> 30:25.224
No, no, no, he didn't say that.
He didn't say that.

30:34.566 --> 30:36.678
What's going on?
Help... Help me.

30:36.702 --> 30:40.072
Victor.

30:50.249 --> 30:53.495
You know, I left
my social class back in 2009

30:53.519 --> 30:56.055
when I finished high school.

31:28.887 --> 31:30.398
It's good to debate ideas.

31:30.422 --> 31:32.334
Don't you think?

31:32.358 --> 31:35.103
In my house, I could never
talk about my anarchism

31:35.127 --> 31:37.763
without my father going insane.

32:23.042 --> 32:26.054
Are you... is that...
Is everything...

32:26.078 --> 32:27.722
Is it because of what
I said about America?

32:27.746 --> 32:29.357
Is that the problem?

32:29.381 --> 32:31.693
No, what do you mean?
Well, what do you mean?

32:31.717 --> 32:35.197
What do you mean?
America?

32:35.221 --> 32:38.390
Yeah.

32:45.564 --> 32:48.234
Yeah, I'll have some.

33:15.227 --> 33:17.039
What is this?

33:17.063 --> 33:18.873
This?
What is that?

33:20.266 --> 33:23.178
That tells me nothing.

33:23.202 --> 33:25.013
Well, I don't know
how to say it in English.

33:25.037 --> 33:26.881
It's chinchulines.

33:26.905 --> 33:28.550
Is it a tapeworm?

33:28.574 --> 33:30.485
Why don't you eat?

33:30.509 --> 33:31.586
'Cause it looks horrible.

33:31.610 --> 33:33.755
You have to. Do you want this?

33:33.779 --> 33:35.914
Yeah, I'll take salad, yeah.

33:48.594 --> 33:53.741
So, how are you doing, cousin?

33:53.765 --> 33:58.413
I'm good. I think
I'm adjusting really well.

33:58.437 --> 34:00.248
Okay.
And everyone likes me.

34:00.272 --> 34:01.416
Yes.

34:01.440 --> 34:03.185
I feel like...
We should toast.

34:03.209 --> 34:05.853
Mm-hmm.
To Aunt Mabel.

34:05.877 --> 34:08.414
What do you think?

34:15.587 --> 34:18.190
We're going out?
We're going out there?

34:29.467 --> 34:31.803
What's going on?

34:33.572 --> 34:36.275
Is he burning paintings?

35:01.300 --> 35:03.369
Victor!

35:07.239 --> 35:08.583
Oh!

35:12.878 --> 35:14.356
I'm sorry.

35:14.380 --> 35:16.924
Holy shit.

35:16.948 --> 35:18.726
I'm sorry.
It's not funny.

35:20.118 --> 35:22.554
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

35:54.220 --> 35:58.065
I-I-I hate
to ask you guys to do this,

35:58.089 --> 36:01.569
but can we have
a conversation in English?

36:01.593 --> 36:05.039
This is a fucking nightmare.

36:09.968 --> 36:11.613
Yes.

36:11.637 --> 36:14.416
You know, when...
When he started showing

36:14.440 --> 36:17.385
in my mom's gallery,

36:17.409 --> 36:20.355
I used to write essays
for the exhibition's catalogues,

36:20.379 --> 36:23.891
and just writing for him
was a nightmare.

36:23.915 --> 36:25.860
I quit.

36:25.884 --> 36:30.064
It was the only way
I could be his girlfriend.

36:30.088 --> 36:33.034
I don't know how you do it.

36:33.058 --> 36:35.461
All that work gone to waste.

36:37.463 --> 36:39.841
Well, you know what?
I'm leaving tomorrow.

36:39.865 --> 36:41.609
So I wish you good luck.

36:41.633 --> 36:43.245
What do you mean, leaving?
¿Qué?

36:43.269 --> 36:46.248
And then you work, your trabajo?

36:47.506 --> 36:50.017
We can't do new work
in two days.

36:50.041 --> 36:51.353
What about the exhibition?

36:51.377 --> 36:53.821
Flor, I don't think it's cool

36:53.845 --> 36:55.423
that you quit
when things get rough.

36:55.447 --> 36:57.191
But you said
that you quit before.

36:57.215 --> 36:59.727
Yes, but it's different.

36:59.751 --> 37:01.229
I'm... I'm his girlfriend.

37:01.253 --> 37:06.858
Well, I guess I'm not,
so I'm leaving tomorrow.

37:12.898 --> 37:15.100
Morning.
Morning.

37:17.703 --> 37:20.348
Where's the rooster?

37:20.372 --> 37:23.050
You don't need a rooster
to lay eggs.

37:23.074 --> 37:24.386
You don't?

37:24.410 --> 37:27.322
The hens just do it fine
by themselves.

37:27.346 --> 37:28.923
I can't believe
I didn't know that.

37:28.947 --> 37:30.758
Hmm.

37:30.782 --> 37:34.996
Listen, uh, the situation
got complicated last night.

37:35.020 --> 37:37.265
Yeah.
Yes.

37:37.289 --> 37:38.766
Yeah.
Hmm.

37:38.790 --> 37:43.338
Um, you know, you won't
have any trouble from me.

37:43.362 --> 37:44.839
No, no, mm.

37:44.863 --> 37:48.376
I know I told you
that you could stay here, but...

37:48.400 --> 37:50.578
Wait.
It's really difficult.

37:50.602 --> 37:52.380
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

37:52.404 --> 37:55.717
You know, he burned those
paintings on purpose, right?

37:55.741 --> 38:00.154
Yes, but, um, that's not
your problem.

38:00.178 --> 38:02.690
I mean, maybe if Victor
wasn't in the picture,

38:02.714 --> 38:05.393
things would be different.

38:05.417 --> 38:08.663
But I'm sorry.
You have to go.

38:08.687 --> 38:10.264
Start thinking
of friends of friends.

38:10.288 --> 38:13.200
You can't...
You can't just do that.

38:13.224 --> 38:17.038
You can't just use me
when it's convenient for you.

38:17.062 --> 38:18.540
But what do you mean "use you"?

38:18.564 --> 38:20.708
You're here
because you need my help.

38:20.732 --> 38:23.745
Really?

38:23.769 --> 38:26.738
You sure I'm not here
because you want to upset him?

38:29.274 --> 38:31.710
I have no choice. I-I'm sorry.

39:20.792 --> 39:23.204
You can't just fabricate
a full-time project.

39:23.228 --> 39:24.706
He said it himself.
But...

39:24.730 --> 39:26.207
His... No, his work was trash,
so he burned it.

39:26.231 --> 39:27.942
That's the concept.
It's genius.

39:27.966 --> 39:29.243
It doesn't work that way.
Why doesn't it work that way?

39:29.267 --> 39:30.712
You used to write his essays.

39:30.736 --> 39:32.447
You can justify anything.

39:32.471 --> 39:34.115
Are you telling me
that you would rather

39:34.139 --> 39:36.551
spend weeks up there with Victor

39:36.575 --> 39:37.852
pissing and moaning
around the house?

39:37.876 --> 39:39.521
I've seen that dynamic, okay?

39:39.545 --> 39:40.922
I know what that looks like.

39:40.946 --> 39:42.557
So?

39:42.581 --> 39:43.925
So...
So.

39:43.949 --> 39:45.427
So all we have to do
is convince him

39:45.451 --> 39:47.361
that it's a good idea.

39:47.385 --> 39:50.064
All of us working for him?
Yeah.

39:50.088 --> 39:52.791
He'll love that, for sure.

40:42.741 --> 40:46.244
I'll talk to him.

40:51.950 --> 40:54.195
He's hard to get, you know,
sometimes,

40:54.219 --> 40:56.864
because he's a genius.

40:56.888 --> 40:59.625
Yeah, I'm sure that's it.

41:00.526 --> 41:04.038
Alex...

41:04.062 --> 41:06.908
if this works, would you mind

41:06.932 --> 41:13.180
if I don't tell my parents
that it was your idea?

41:13.204 --> 41:17.051
Your... your par...
your parents?

41:17.075 --> 41:18.553
Yeah, no, that's fine.
Yeah, yeah, totally.

41:18.577 --> 41:20.855
'Cause, you know,
sometimes it's hard

41:20.879 --> 41:23.424
for them to understand
what I'm doing here.

41:23.448 --> 41:27.529
Yeah, that makes a lot of sense.

41:27.553 --> 41:31.432
You're so fucking cool,
you know? Thank you.

41:31.456 --> 41:35.269
That's a very thoughtful thing
for you to say.

41:35.293 --> 41:37.438
He's in.

42:03.889 --> 42:06.267
What'd he say?

42:06.291 --> 42:08.727
Like this.

42:59.077 --> 43:01.656
Hey, so, uh, Victor was saying

43:01.680 --> 43:04.525
that since fragments
are accidents

43:04.549 --> 43:07.061
we shouldn't try
to understand it

43:07.085 --> 43:10.531
because, you know, accidents
mustn't be comprehended.

43:10.555 --> 43:12.199
Okay. Bueno.

43:12.223 --> 43:14.368
Just tell us
how he wants it, okay?

43:14.392 --> 43:18.840
Okay, so, um, just group
them by color and size.

43:18.864 --> 43:21.466
Okay?

43:27.906 --> 43:31.943
I love her so much.
Just so much.

43:44.022 --> 43:46.701
I'm an addict!

43:46.725 --> 43:48.335
It's all I can think about.

43:48.359 --> 43:50.537
You can't just
take it away from me.

43:50.561 --> 43:51.873
It's unfair.

43:51.897 --> 43:53.507
You have to, like,
wean me off of it.

43:53.531 --> 43:56.010
You are in rehab here. Okay?

43:56.034 --> 43:58.412
And you will not tweet, period.

43:58.436 --> 44:01.282
Yeah, that's my point.
I'm down here.

44:01.306 --> 44:03.384
I'm in the jungles
of South Africa.

44:03.408 --> 44:04.752
South Africa.
And I can't...

44:04.776 --> 44:06.053
I can't even tweet about it.

44:06.077 --> 44:07.855
I'm like a "Swiss
Family Robinson" member.

44:07.879 --> 44:10.591
I'm so proud. Look at you.

44:10.615 --> 44:12.193
A changed man.

44:12.217 --> 44:15.029
Just keep these memories
and feelings for yourself, okay?

44:15.053 --> 44:16.530
Oh.
Oh.

44:16.554 --> 44:19.224
Oh.

44:31.236 --> 44:34.248
He's a real man's man.

44:34.272 --> 44:35.216
He reminds me of my dad.

44:35.240 --> 44:37.551
Shh.

44:37.575 --> 44:38.585
You should be
ashamed of yourself.

44:38.609 --> 44:39.854
Shh, shh, shh.

44:39.878 --> 44:41.422
What is he?
He's like 65, right?

44:41.446 --> 44:42.890
No.
I'm just saying.

44:42.914 --> 44:45.592
No.

44:45.616 --> 44:47.895
He could be your grandfather.

44:47.919 --> 44:49.163
No.

44:49.187 --> 44:50.431
Easily.

44:50.455 --> 44:53.868
My father. No.
You just said it.

44:53.892 --> 44:56.427
You can't take it back.

45:25.857 --> 45:28.093
Bueno.

45:33.198 --> 45:35.709
Is everything...
Is everything all right?

45:35.733 --> 45:38.245
Yes, yes.
Perfectly fine.

45:38.269 --> 45:39.747
We will do the last one.

45:39.771 --> 45:42.850
When we finish with these two,
we will be done.

45:42.874 --> 45:44.685
Thank you so much, Alex.

45:44.709 --> 45:47.354
Yeah, no, it's fun.
I'm having fun with it.

45:47.378 --> 45:49.256
It's good.

45:58.957 --> 46:01.568
He's saying that he's happy
that you're happy.

46:01.592 --> 46:03.370
Like, we're all happy.

46:03.394 --> 46:06.707
Good. That's good. You ready?

46:06.731 --> 46:10.277
Yes.

46:10.301 --> 46:12.971
No sé.

46:32.891 --> 46:35.169
I wanted to give you something.

46:35.193 --> 46:39.540
It's a little reward
for adapting here.

46:39.564 --> 46:41.108
I think I'm doing
a pretty good job.

46:41.132 --> 46:42.743
I'm enjoying the unplugged life.

46:42.767 --> 46:45.246
Mm-hmm. Where is it?

46:45.270 --> 46:48.115
It's here.

46:48.139 --> 46:53.420
And this.

46:53.444 --> 46:55.689
What is this?

46:55.713 --> 46:58.993
Is this what I think it is?

46:59.017 --> 47:01.062
Oh, my gosh. That's so cool.

47:01.086 --> 47:02.729
You like it?

47:02.753 --> 47:06.033
Well, it was my father's.

47:06.057 --> 47:08.535
And this, too.
He was an architect.

47:08.559 --> 47:11.096
And he spent hours
and hours drawing.

47:13.631 --> 47:15.709
Oh, my gosh.

47:15.733 --> 47:16.944
Wow, look at this.

47:16.968 --> 47:18.279
You're just gonna
give this to me?

47:18.303 --> 47:19.680
Yes.
Are you sure?

47:19.704 --> 47:22.149
Yes, I am sure.
Of course, it's a present.

47:22.173 --> 47:24.852
Thank you.
A reward.

47:24.876 --> 47:26.553
What's that?

47:26.577 --> 47:30.091
I keep it.

47:30.115 --> 47:31.692
Thank you so much.
This is...

47:31.716 --> 47:33.360
You're welcome.

47:33.384 --> 47:34.896
This is really cool.

47:34.920 --> 47:38.123
I haven't drawn in ages.
I can't wait.

49:23.228 --> 49:24.571
The self.

49:24.595 --> 49:26.540
In "Camera Lucida,"
published in 1980,

49:26.564 --> 49:28.175
Roland Barthes describes

49:28.199 --> 49:30.777
how our personality splits
in front of the camera,

49:30.801 --> 49:32.779
unfolding our various selves.

49:32.803 --> 49:34.281
Like Roland,
I suddenly felt like

49:34.305 --> 49:36.350
I was three different people
at the same time.

49:36.374 --> 49:37.884
One, the one I thought I was.

49:37.908 --> 49:40.254
Two, the one I wanted Sofia
to think I was.

49:40.278 --> 49:43.090
And three, the one I feared
Sofia saw in me.

49:43.114 --> 49:45.092
All three combined
in the same body

49:45.116 --> 49:47.328
posing in front
of the camera about to snap.

49:47.352 --> 49:48.762
The timer was ticking.

49:48.786 --> 49:50.597
I wanted Sofia's idea of me
to be

49:50.621 --> 49:52.499
the self I thought I was,
or in all honesty,

49:52.523 --> 49:54.901
the self I thought
I could potentially become.

49:54.925 --> 49:58.005
But a feeling of inauthenticity
started to rush in.

49:58.029 --> 50:00.007
I tried to fight it,
compensating with a pose

50:00.031 --> 50:03.044
that would avoid the idea
I feared Sofia had of me,

50:03.068 --> 50:04.411
but it was too late.

50:04.435 --> 50:06.137
That afternoon,
the picture was taken.

50:30.395 --> 50:33.631
Is that coke?
No, it's MDMA.

50:40.305 --> 50:42.349
You guys are...
You guys are doing ecstasy?

50:42.373 --> 50:43.717
You guys are gonna do ecstasy?

50:43.741 --> 50:45.519
No, MDMA.
Yeah, it's the same thing.

50:45.543 --> 50:47.488
No, it's not.
Are we in 1996?

50:47.512 --> 50:49.090
Yes, we are.
We are?

50:49.114 --> 50:50.424
